SubLib
====================
http://sublib.sf.net


RELEASE PROCEDURE
=================

	1. Revise base project files
	2. Bump the version
	3. Commit changes and tag
	4. Create source package
	5. Create screenshots
	6. Release packages
	7. Verify integrity
	8. Notify


1. Revise base project files
============================

	- CREDITS
	- README
	- NEWS
	- ChangeLog using svn2log:
		svn log -v --xml https://svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/gsubtitles/trunk/gnome-subtitles | svn2log.py -s -O -H -p '/(branches/[^/]+|trunk)/' -o changelog.txt


2. Bump the version
===================

	- configure.in: ACINIT


3. Commit changes and tag
=========================

	- Commit changes for the release
	- Tag the release with (replace VERSION):
		svn copy https://svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/gsubtitles/trunk/gnome-subtitles https://svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/gsubtitles/tags/gnome-subtitles-VERSION -m "Tagging the VERSION release."


4. Create source package
========================

	- Autogen autotools files with:
		autogen.sh
	- Package with:
		make dist
	- Test package with:
		tar xzf gnome-subtitles-*.tar.gz && cd gnome-subtitles-* && ./configure && make && nant


5. Create Screenshots
=====================

	- Screenshots are to be created only if any of the windows/dialogs' aspect changes
	- Create screenshots with:
		gnome-screenshot --window --include-border --delay=5 --border-effect=shadow
	- Screenshots for website:
		- Flatten images with white background
		- Remove black pixels from window corners
		- Correct the shadow on the top right corner (white paint with 30% opacity)
	- Screenshots for sf.net project page:
		- Rescale to maximum 640x480 with cubic method
		- Sharpen with a factor of 30


6. Release packages
===================

	- Add to File Release System in Sourceforge
	- Send Email Release Notice in the File Release System


7. Verify integrity
===================

	- Download released files to temporary dir and cd to that dir
	- Create the checksum with the locally created file and use it to check the downloaded files, with:
		md5sum gnome-subtitles-VERSION.tar.gz > md5result && mv md5result /path/to/downloaded/package/dir && cd /path/to/downloaded/package/dir && md5sum --check md5result && rm md5result
	- Build the source package using the "Test package with" commands above
	

8. Notify
=========

	- Post screenshots in Sourceforge project page
	- Post news in Sourceforge project page
	- Update Gnome Subtitles website:
		About
		Download
		Screenshots (upload new screenshots to the project's web area)
		News
	- Update freshmeat page
	- Send mail to the Gnome Announce mailing list
	- Send mail to the Gnome Subtitles mailing list
	- Update Gnome-files.org page
	- Update Gentoo Ebuild
	- Update threads in distro's forums, RNL forum
